# Default Rhei State Machine

These are the default states used by Rhei plans when no project-specific state machine is declared (i.e., when `**States:**` is omitted, or when the project's `docs/states.yaml` mirrors this set). This mirrors the built-in `rhei` machine (version 3.0).

Every task node starts in `draft` (the profile's `initial`). Agents claim a task with `rhei next` — which sets `**Assignee:**` without changing the state — then work in the current state, call `rhei transition` to advance, and call `rhei complete` to finalize with a result message.

Each state carries an instruction for executing agents:

- `draft` — Task requires analysis before execution. Pick up when all `**Prior:**` tasks are in a terminal state. Analyze the project and write a concrete description of what should be done. Transition to `pending` when the description is finalized.
- `pending` — Ready for implementation. An `**Assignee:**` on a pending task means work is actively in progress. Implement the task and any child task nodes, logging progress per child task. When implementation is complete and self-tested, either call `rhei complete` to finish directly or transition to `agent-review` when a separate review pass is required.
- `agent-review` — A separate reviewing agent inspects the result against the task description, child task nodes, and repository conventions. On pass, transition to `human-review` (or `completed` if no human gate is required). On fail, transition to `agent-review-fix` with concrete findings.
- `agent-review-fix` — The implementing agent addresses reviewer findings only — no scope expansion. Transition back to `agent-review` after applying fixes.
- `human-review` (gating) — Stop all agent work on this task. Wait for a human to approve, request changes, or edit the plan. Do not transition out of this state autonomously.
- `completed` (final) — Treat as immutable. Do not re-open, re-run, or modify unless the user explicitly requests it.
- `cancelled` (final) — Skip entirely. Do not execute, review, or reference as a prerequisite for new work.

## Declared transitions

- `draft` → `pending`, `cancelled`
- `pending` → `agent-review`, `human-review`, `completed`, `cancelled`
- `agent-review` → `agent-review-fix`, `human-review`, `completed`
- `agent-review-fix` → `agent-review`, `cancelled`
- `human-review` → `pending`, `completed`, `cancelled`

No other transitions are legal.

## Profiles and node policy

The default machine defines a single profile `default-rhei` with `initial: draft` and an `allowed` set covering every non-terminal and terminal state above. Both `node_policy.root` and `node_policy.default` resolve to that profile, so every node kind (including the implicit `rhei` root) shares the same flow.
# States Definition for Markdown Plan Compiler
# This file defines the valid states for tasks and the allowed transitions
# between them. The CLI can print this machine with `rhei states`.

name: rhei
version: 2.0

states:
  draft:
    description: Task requires analysis before execution — the agent studies the project and writes a concrete task description.
    instructions: |
      Pick up when all **Prior:** tasks are `completed`. Analyze the current
      state of the project and determine the most elegant way to accomplish
      the task. Based on that analysis, write a description of what should be
      done. Transition to `pending` once the description is finalized.
    initial: true

  pending:
    description: Task is ready for implementation. An **Assignee** on a pending task means work is actively in progress.
    instructions: |
      Pick up when all **Prior:** tasks are `completed`. Implement the task and
      its subtasks, logging progress per subtask. When implementation is
      complete and self-tested, either run `rhei complete` to finish directly
      or transition to `agent-review` when a separate review pass is required.

  agent-review:
    description: A separate reviewing agent inspects the result.
    instructions: |
      Review the implementation against the task description, subtasks, and
      repository conventions. On pass, transition to `human-review` (or
      `completed` if no human gate is required). On fail, transition to
      `agent-review-fix` with concrete findings.

  agent-review-fix:
    description: The implementing agent addresses reviewer findings.
    instructions: |
      Address the reviewer's findings only — no scope expansion. After
      applying fixes, transition back to `agent-review` for re-review.

  human-review:
    description: Work is paused pending human inspection.
    gating: true
    instructions: |
      Stop all agent work on this task. Wait for a human to approve, request
      changes, or edit the rhei. Do not transition out of this state
      autonomously.

  completed:
    description: Task finished successfully.
    instructions: |
      Treat as immutable. Do not re-open, re-run, or modify unless the user
      explicitly requests it.
    final: true

  cancelled:
    description: Task is no longer needed.
    instructions: |
      Skip entirely. Do not execute, review, or reference as a prerequisite
      for new work.
    final: true

# Explicit transition rules. Any transition not listed here is forbidden.
transitions:
  - from: draft
    to: pending
    description: Task analysis complete, description finalized and ready for implementation
  - from: draft
    to: cancelled
    description: Task abandoned before analysis
  - from: pending
    to: agent-review
    description: Implementation complete, ready for automated review
  - from: pending
    to: human-review
    description: Implementation complete, requires human inspection
  - from: pending
    to: completed
    description: Implementation complete, no review required
  - from: pending
    to: cancelled
    description: Task abandoned during implementation
  - from: agent-review
    to: agent-review-fix
    description: Review found issues, implementing agent must apply fixes
  - from: agent-review
    to: human-review
    description: Review passed but human gate required before completion
  - from: agent-review
    to: completed
    description: Review passed, task finished successfully
  - from: agent-review-fix
    to: agent-review
    description: Fixes applied, re-submit for review
  - from: agent-review-fix
    to: cancelled
    description: Task abandoned during fix phase
  - from: human-review
    to: pending
    description: Human requested rework, task returns to implementation
  - from: human-review
    to: completed
    description: Human approved the work
  - from: human-review
    to: cancelled
    description: Human decided to abandon the task
